                        CROSS ACCOUNT S3 DATA REPLICATION
	Create two accounts:
•	Account A ~ Which will contain source bucket
                   ~ Enable versioning
•	Account B ~ Which will contain destination bucket 
                   ~ Enable versioning
	Create an IAM policy for the source bucket-:
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": [
        "s3:GetReplicationConfiguration",
        "s3:ListBucket",
        "s3:GetBucketVersioning"
      ],
      "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::<SOURCE-BUCKET>"
    },
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": [
        "s3:GetObjectVersion",
        "s3:GetObjectVersionAcl",
        "s3:GetObjectVersionForReplication",
        "s3:GetObjectTagging",
        "s3:GetObjectVersionTagging"
      ],
      "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::<SOURCE-BUCKET>/*"
    },
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": [
        "s3:ReplicateObject",
        "s3:ReplicateDelete",
        "s3:ReplicateTags",
        "s3:ObjectOwnerOverrideToBucketOwner"
      ],
      "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::<DESTINATION-BUCKET>/*"
    }
  ]
}

	Create a bucket policy for destination bucket to accept the replication
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Principal": {
        "AWS": "arn:aws:iam::<ACCOUNT-A-ID>:role/<REPLICATION-ROLE-NAME>"
      },
      "Action": [
        "s3:ReplicateObject",
        "s3:ReplicateDelete",
        "s3:ReplicateTags",
        "s3:ObjectOwnerOverrideToBucketOwner"
      ],
      "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::<DESTINATION-BUCKET>/*"
    }
  ]
}

	Create a replication rule for source bucket
•	Go to Source bucket > Management > Replication
•	Scope: Entire bucket / prefix
•	IAM Role: Select the one created above
•	Destination bucket: Enter Account B bucket ARN (cross-account)
•	Enable ownership override (recommended)
 
 
